  "plain_summary": "The Inflation Reduction Act of 2025 would completely get rid of the Inflation Reduction Act that was passed in 2022. It would also take back any money from that old law that has not been spent yet. This new bill has the same name as the old one but does the opposite by canceling all the programs and rules from 2022. The government would stop spending money on anything that was part of the original Inflation Reduction Act.",
